A man has died while another is fighting for his life at Kinangop Mission Hospital after they were beaten by a mob at Matura shopping centre in Ol Kalou on Tuesday morning.Nyandarua Central police boss Wilson Kosgei yesterday said Laban Muigai, 45, and Samuel Njoroge, 25, were among four men, who were seen by residents attempting to break into shops in Matura at 4am.Residents mobilised and confronted the four, who are said to be from Nyairoko in Nyandarua West. Two escaped, but Muigai and Njoroge were cornered by the mob.Police were notified by the area chief and they arrived in time to save the two from being lynched. They were rushed to Kinangop Mission Hospital with serious injuries, but Muigai succumbed on Tuesday evening.